Art Fight
By Kelly Crow
Word Count: 564

Steven Spielberg earned praise three months ago when he told authorities he'd uncovered a stolen Norman Rockwell painting in his own collection. But now, the case is evolving into a complicated legal battle. This past week, art dealers with earlier ties to the work went to court to claim it back.

These new developments pit two art dealers -- both of whom claim ownership prior to Mr. Spielberg's acquisition -- against each other. That's throwing the fate of the painting into limbo.

